{
  "text": "For cloning of the 5' terminal regions of both RNA1 and RNA2, 5' RACE (rapid amplification of cDNA ends) was performed according to the methods of [CITATION_1] . The sequences of the primers used in the BdMoV genome analysis are available upon request. Kondo et al. 7 The blood-sucking bug (Rhodnius prolixus) individuals, which were kindly provided by H. Kanuka of Jikei University School of Medicine (Tokyo, Japan), and the commercially available seeds of chickpeas (Cicer arietinum cv. unknown) were used.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "24742184"
